Although the expectation value of the spinor obeys the classical Dirac
equation (), large quantum fluctuations of 
around   its  expectation   value  might   invalidate   the  classical
approximation.   In  our particular  case,  the  only observable  that
enters the  classical Einstein equations is the  energy density, which
in our classical treatment is
 
We  want to  find  out whether  the  expectation value  of the  energy
density   is  well
approximated  by ().  At this  stage, one  has to
face   a  well-known   problem.  The   vacuum  expectation   value  of
