the following relation should hold,
 
In the bosonic case, the  states that satisfy inequalities analogous to
()  have  large   occupation  numbers.   As  the
largest  occupation number  of fermion  modes is  one, it  is commonly
believed that fermionic physical  states cannot satisfy relations such
as ().  This turns out not to be the case.


Let  and  be two complex numbers and let  be the state
 
Here,  is the vacuum and  is
a zero-momentum one-particle state.  The state is normalized if
 
The  spinor operator can be expanded  in creation and
